      "message": "[Critical] Line 43: The importer trusts the JSON-controlled `file` value and joins it directly with `REPO_ROOT`. A crafted JSON can use an absolute path or `../` traversal to make the script parse and rewrite arbitrary writable XML files. Derive the target from a validated language code or ensure the resolved path stays under `translations/` and matches `jami_client_qt_\u003clang\u003e.ts`.\n```suggestion\n    rel_path \u003d payload[\u0027file\u0027]\n    ts_path \u003d os.path.abspath(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, rel_path))\n    translations_dir \u003d os.path.abspath(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \u0027translations\u0027))\n    if not ts_path.startswith(translations_dir + os.sep):\n        raise ValueError(\u0027translation file must be under translations/\u0027)\n```",
